Details.Education:
Per the Office of Personnel Management Qualifications Standards, education may be substituted for experience at the GS-11 grade level as follows: Successful completion of a Ph.D. or equivalent doctoral degree;
or
Successful completion of three full years of progressively higher level graduate education leading to a Ph.D. or equivalent degree;
or
Successful completion of an LL.M. degree that is related to the position being filled. https://www.usajobs.gov/Help/working-in-government/unique-hiringpaths/students/federal-occupations-by-college-major/;
or
A combination of experience and graduate education as described above that equates to one year of experience. The percentage of required education plus the percentage of required experience must equal one hundred percent.

MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-07 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following: Advance experience applying a wide range of classification and position management theories, concepts, practices, laws, policies, rules, regulations, precedents and procedures required to perform a variety of difficult and complex assignments, including OPM classification principles and the proper use of OPM classification standards and guides;
Advance experience researching and applying findings to provide solutions to a wide range of HR management functions;
Advance experience with written and verbal communication to research and present findings in the functional area of classification, developing functional trainings and preparing policies and/or written instructions;
Experience providing a full range of services requiring research and analysis. Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-05 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following: Experience applying a wide range of classification and position management theories, concepts, practices, laws, policies, rules, regulations, precedents and procedures required to perform a variety of difficult and complex assignments;
Experience researching and applying findings to provide solutions to a wide range of HR management functions;
Experience researching a variety of HR related subjects and answering a variety of HR related questions;
Experience with written and verbal communication to research and present findings in the functional area of classification. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management web site: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.
